Am 01-Jul-99 schrieb John Niclasen:

>Hi Sam!

>On 29-Jun-99, Sam Jordan wrote:
>> Certainly there are ways to reduce the bus traffic. The
>> best one is to maximize the usage of
>> triangle-strips/fans.

>Can you give a short explanation of, what strips/fans are?

You can find information about strips/fans in the OpenGL
documentation. Basically a strip is a sequence of triangles,
where triangle n has 2 vertices in common with triangle n-1.
This sequence forms a mesh of triangles, and for every triangle
only one new vertex is introduced.

Strips and fans are different, as in a fan every triangle
shares one vertex with all others, while this isn't the case
for strips.

