1. Is there anything I need to know about this mailing list?
------------------------------------------------------------

As with most public discussion forums, you should follow standard netique=
tte.
Briefly:

=B7Don't post off-topic posts.

=B7Keep posts as short as possible and to the point.

=B7Don't quote entire mails when replying to posts, only quote the releva=
nt
 parts. This reduces bandwidth use and makes it easier to read your repli=
es.

=B7Don't shout (i.e. USE ALL CAPITAL LETTERS) or swear, people will take =
more
 notice if you calmly state your arguments.

=B7The list's primary language is English. If you want everyone to listen=
 to you,
 then English is the language to use.

=B7Never post spam (unsolicited email, usually trying to sell or advertis=
e
 something).

=B7Do not discuss illegal software. This includes QuakePPC and any stolen
 source code.

=B7Do not post HTML.

=B7Do not post binaries (programs, pictures etc).

=B7Do not let your posts get bigger than about 20-30k, at the very most.

=B7Do not post about Threads That Would Not Die (see section 1.3).

=B7Don't just answer something for the sake of argument or to save face. =
We
 are all wrong sometimes. If your answer does not advance the argument at
 all or simply repeats something already said, don't bother.

=B7Never take things personally, even if someone personally insults you j=
ust
 ignore it. Replying will only lower yourself to their level, and all
 others probably resent them for making the post anyway.

=B7Use abbreviations to clarify yourself. Use IMHO for opinions and IIRC =
when
 quoting from memory. This way no one can misunderstand your meaning when
 making posts that may not be entirely factual.

=B7Don't use excessive emotions. :DDDDDDDDDDD is no better than :) or a
 simple <g>.

=B7If you are unsure your post is relevant or on-topic, keep it short and=
 to
 the point and only post if really necessary.

=B7If you change the subject of a post you are replying to significantly,
 remember to change the subject line too.

=B7Some people are very busy, so don't take it personally if they don't
 answer your posts.

=B7Don't post religious or political beliefs. There are plenty of newsgro=
ups
 for that.

It is a good idea to read the list for a few days or weeks before posting=
, as
this will give you a good idea of how the list works and what is/is not
acceptable.

Above all, remember that the list is there to help people and to have
interesting and friendly discussions on. Always keep that in mind, and ev=
en if
people don't agree with you just remember that everyone is entitled to th=
eir
opinion. If there was no disagreement or discussion, life would be very
boring!


