> be necessary to check n^2 triangles, therefore some hashtable
> appraoch is necessary. But even this didn't help here...

Did you have a look at LEDA? That's the "Library of Efficient Data
structures and Algorithms". The problem is that vertices might differ
slightly, so you are basically interested in a closest neigbourhood
search. In LEDA, this is done using so-called "kd-trees", that stands for
"k-dimensional tree". Using a kd-tree, it should be possible to merge
sufficently near vertices into one...

Just out of interest, do you intend to do this fan/strip generation
on-the-fly while loading, or as a preprocessing step?

> I think it's a real challenge to write a good and fast strip/fan
> generator, so anybody who likes challenges is welcome to face it.

Maybe a job for vbender the great? In asm, of course :) SCNR

