Scandoubler problem

When i changed my oldie C=1084S to scandoubler for CV3D card (Phase5) & VGA
monitor,  i  found out that many, especialy new demos/games producing trash
display.   Because  all  OS  screens  and majority of other things don't do
that,  then  i  suspect  any  bug  in copperlist.  After asking for help my
friend  Zeleny,  he  provided quickly solution - problem is in COLOR bit in
BPLCON0.   It  MUST be always SET !!!  Otherwise there will be problem with
synchonisation  on  all  Amigas  with  scandoubler  except  PicassoIV FliFi
because  this  works  as a grabing device, istead of all others ones, which
only double vertical frequency.

Programmers, please, correct your code, color bit MUST be set!!!
Othervise users see ONLY flicking fucking dirt on screen, so...

Many, many ppl don't know that, and unusable demos/games are result of that,
for example Ride/Jamie Skarla, Relic/Nerve Axis, EraserHead/Maq,
Dreizehn/Oxyron, Goa/TBL, Manipulations by Venus Art, Superautodrome/SCX,
MyKingdom/SCX (last effect in part 2), G-force/PygmyProjects, Cliches/Kalsu,
and many, many others what i delete instead of fixing...
From games i crying for SlamTilt, but now working!!! Also CannonFodder HD
fix have some that troubles, IIRC... etc... I'm not much into games anyway.
Oh, yes, BrianTheLion have some ugly flicks in loading, so...

With hacking experinece, i find that many (99.9%) cooperlists can be located
and fixed, just search for "fffffffe" (end of cooper) or "01800000"
(black back) and then look out for start of cooper and Bplcon setting
(resolution, etc, etc...) and change bytes, for example from "010000" to
"010002" or "010050" to "010052" and vice versa...
This way we fix 99% of mentioned products, so =)   Some working now like
a charm (Ride, Cliches, Goa, EraserHead...), some still having one or two
cooperlists, what are probably builded "on the fly", so we can't fix that
(or that will be hard), as Relic (still two flicks, but is VISIBLE NOW!),
G-force or Manipulations... or some parts of SlamTilt intro...

If  you  are  still  not  persuaded,  watch  the demo Ride on an Amiga with
scandoubler  !!!



For more info, contact me privately, pls. Thx.

See ya!

