While it would be nice if we could all just get along, I think you need
to delve a little deeper before you label the entire human race as stupid.

Consider that humans have evolved over a long period of time to take
their position as the dominant species on this planet. The characteristics
that got us to this point are the very same characteristics that you're
now labelling as stupid.

Now consider how long humans have been living in civilized societies.
As time goes, it's barely a tick on the evolutionary clock. The fact
that we don't all go out and murder each other is not because we've
suddenly lost our predatory urges (I think most people have at least
*thought* of killing someone they didn't like), but because societies
as a whole take care of our basic needs, keep us busy, and try to
deter unwanted behaviour with the threat of punishment. The fact
is, we are an aggressive species. It comes out in many things we
do, not just in violent behaviour, but in sports, competition in the
work place, getting the highest score/mark, the most amount of money
and material wealth, our obsession with looks to attract the opposite
sex; the list goes on and on.

