>> example without problems. I think that it crashes because of wrong
>> structures alignment in system includes.
> 
> Yes, it's exactly the problem. During the compilation stage I get many 
> warning about struct etc...

The warnings you got where caused by something different. this example
includes only protos for system functions (ie. <clib/dos_protos.h>

there are  definitions of functions, but the structures that are passed as
args are not defined like this:

foo(struct BitMap *b);

When there was no definition of BitMap you will get warning 

warning: `struct BitMap' declared inside parameter list
warning: its scope is only this definition or declaration,
warning: which is probably not what you want.

It has no matter (pointer is a pointer, no matter how defined).

You should include <proto/dos.h> (for example) to get rid of those warnings.

This is also needed because you need inlines for system calls.

Regards
 Sebastian

