The speed increase depends heavily on the vertical refresh
rate of the monitor when using a certain screen mode. That's
because synchronized double-buffering usually runs at an
integral part of the vertical frequency, and therefore below
the theoretical frame-rate. Now the vertical frequency might
only be few below the theoretical frame-rate or it might be
much below. Therefore always take care when doing such
measurements.

