use Checkelf (by Steffan Heauser) Should be on paladin site
(cs.tu-berlin.de/~paladin) It will show all undefined symbols. Or edit

/ade/lib/gcc-lib/ppc-amigaos/egcs-2.91.66/specs (this is my location, if you
got another egcs version it will be in another directory)

and replace line:

*link:
-r <something more here, do not change this>

with:

*link:
%{!warpup:-r} <leave the rest of this line unchanged>

Then the linker will show all undefined symbols, when -warpup parameter will
be used.

Regards
 Sebastian

